gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 116, Knicks 113
gameRecap.excerpt: Devin Booker nailed a 3 pointer with 1.7 seconds remaining to lift the Suns over the Knicks, 116-113. Booker recorded 28 points, 11 assists, and five rebounds for the Suns, with Eric Gordon adding 25 points (6-9 3PM) and two assists in the victory. Jalen Brunson tallied 35 points, eight assists, and six rebounds for the Knicks in the losing effort.The Suns improve to 11-6 in the regular season, while the Knicks fall to 9-7.
